  "instructions": [
    "Heat the water in a large pot over medium heat until warm.",
    "Add the tahini, lemon juice, garlic, and ginger to the pot and whisk until smooth.",
    "Add the vegetable oil, onion, and mushrooms to the pot and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the spinach and coconut milk to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes.",
    "Season the stew with salt, black pepper, and paprika to taste.",
    "Serve the warm Egyptian water stew hot over rice or with some crusty bread.",
    "Store leftovers in the refrigerator for up to 3 days or freeze for up to 2 months.",
    "When reheating, add more water if the stew has thickened too much.",
    "Adjust the seasoning as needed before serving."
